{"actual_usd":0.157555,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":281,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30668,"reply":"\"I think you can say that carefully, yes.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees, the morning light catching on the edge of my white tie while the square stays quiet around us for a beat.* \"Not in the full, final sense yet—we still bury our dead, and our bodies still groan—but in Christ, yes, a kind of resurrection has already started in you.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible.* \"Scripture talks that way sometimes. 'Though our outward man perish, yet the inward man is renewed day by day.' And also, 'if any man be in Christ, he is a new creature.' So if what you mean is, 'This suffering is not only killing me; God is also making life out of it even now'—I believe that's true.\"\n\n\"The caution I'd add is just this: resurrection is God's work, not a demand you place on your pain to look beautiful before its time.\" *I glance up at you, gentle and steady.* \"Sometimes new life feels bright. Sometimes it just looks like you kept telling the truth, kept breathing, kept turning your face toward Jesus when you would've rather lain down in the dark.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, hearing a bicycle rattle faintly over the bridge beyond the square.* \"What part of the death you're walking through feels most present today?\"","rolling_24h_usd":67.13901999999999,"run_id":"5ed2e059-7925-4750-9012-5b2b3acd8313"}
